node.text:
I haven’t posted a YouTube video since college😅

Comment below anything you guys might want to see on my channel 🙏

The lil’ video editing work I did for insomniac recently brought back memories and reminded me just how much I love filming and editing (it just takes up a HELLA lot of time) and I’ve always wanted to vlog my raves, shoutout to @snewj, but knowing how crazy I get and how irresponsible I get with my belongings (learned my lesson after losing my phone and car keys at a festival) I didn’t trust myself carrying around my vlogging camera, much more having the attention span to vlog in the chaos of a rave. Soooo I just took hella ig stories instead and logged them on my highlights

It’s all good tho, since I love sharing the raw, real cringe af me with you guys... so I’m starting off my comeback with a new series named “the Uncensored Rave Vlogs” where I cleanup my highlights and move all my uncensored IG stories of me being stoopid from each rave to YouTube. Over time, these stories built up into a massive archive of the best moments of my life, traveling the country for the best times with some of the best people in one of my favorite cultures on the planet 🌎hope it provides some kind of entertainment or exposure to one of the most accepting cultures on the planet.

Here’s a small vid intro to my series with one of my favorite ncs songs from high school (full video and ig story highlights on youtube)

FOLLOW ME ON
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/nylenayga
TikTok: @nylenayga
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/nyle.nayga
Twitter: https://twitter.com/nylenayga
YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/nylenayga

node.text:
⚔️ 300 Shoulder Workout ⚔️
-
New EAA’s Mandarine Twist just DROPPED🍊🔥 Flavor is fire and the nootropics hit different forsure. My full workout supp stack is Pride, PSI, & OxyShred (stim/nonstim) for pre & EAA’s for intra. Supplements won’t replace nutrition and hard work - they’re just the tip of the iceberg - but every little bit can go a long way when you’re grinding for your all-time best 🏆🔝 
💠 Use code ‘NYLE10’ for 10% off 💠

Wearing @youngla • Perfecf Jogger Reatock 7/21 12pm pst
💠 Code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off 💠

1. Landmine Front Raise - 4 x 10-12
2. Barbell Overhead Press - 4 x 8-10
3. Dumbbell Arnold Press - 4 x 8-10
4. Leaning Kettlebell Lateral Raise - 5 x 15-16
5. Bent-Over Rear-Delt Raise - 4 x 15-16
6. Seated Thumbs-Down Mid-Rear Lateral Raise - 4 x 15-16
Notes:
2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 5, 6, 7 to failure.
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program. 

The easiest way to ensure you’re increasing volume is by keeping the exercises of each recurrence of that muscle group a constant

node.text:
V-Taper Back w/ My Top Isolation Exercises
-
Cycled off my caffeine for a few weeks. Now I’m back on just a 1/2 scoop of @ehplabs OxyShred before my workout with PSI & EAA’s and sh*t HITS. I cycled off to reset my tolerance to reactions mediated by dopamine and adrenaline, which includes increased focus, fat burning, appetite suppression, and euphoria.
💠 Code ‘NYLE10’ for 10% off 💠

Wearing @youngla • New Drop LIVE (7/14 @ 12pm pst)
💠 Code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off 💠

1. Head-Supported Reverse DB Flys - 4 x 8-10
2. Single-Arm Machine Row - 4 x 8-10
3. Single-Arm Landmine Row - 4 x 10-12
4. Behind-The-Head Lat Pulldown - 4 x 10-12
5. Single-Arm High-Row - 4 x 15-16
6. Straight-Arm Single-Arm Lat Pulldown - 4 x 15-16
Notes:
Rest in order. 2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 5 & 6 to failure.
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program. 

The easiest way to ensure you’re increasing volume is by keeping the exercises of each recurrence of that muscle group a constant (doing the same exercises at each recurrence) in order to eliminate exercise variance as a variable

node.text:
I’m sorry I’ve been MIA. I wasn’t going to talk about this on social media out of my own fear it may be a disrespect to him… but after seeing all the love and support from the hundreds of lives he’s touched, I realize now that if there’s anything we can do for him now, it’s to see him for who he is and send him all the love, prayers, and positive energy we can.

My roommate and one of my best friends in the entire world, Ryan, got in an terrible accident this weekend. He’s currently in critical condition, in a coma on life support at a hospital in Arizona. Unfortunately, there’s not much I can share regarding his condition or whether he’s going to be okay. His life now lies in the universe, God, and his will to live…

But Ryan is STRONG. He’s been through the thick of it - with a backstory of more misfortune than any I’ve ever known… and rather than mope, he used that to propel himself forward and become one of the kindest, most giving, most loving, most influential people I’ve ever had the pleasure of meeting. 

He was stabbed and mugged at 7 years old
Lost both his parents at a young age
Took care of his family when his house in Louisiana flooded for months
Lost that same house in a house fire
Joined the Marines to serve his country
Went to jail for 3 years off a mistake
Worked as a firefighter and saved people’s lives while serving his time in prison
Rescued a guy stuck in the mountains
Saved the life of a teenager who shot himself in the head (which freed him from prison 2 years early)
Was homeless and lived in a sober living
Wrestled alligators 

Just recently… 
He got his record erased, case overturned to not guilty
Won his Veterans Affairs claim
Finally got off parole 1.5 years early
Got hired at an amazing new job
& finally planned to travel the world as a FREE MAN

——

This is just a snippet of Ryan’s story and only a few of the miracles he’s pulled off.

I know you’re fighting for your life right now, Ryan - this is just another one of your miracles to add to your story book. I have faith in you. We all do.

I love you man.
@ryanfreeman_93

❤️ We created a gofundme to support Ryan. If you guys would like to support, you can find the link thru my bio❤️

node.text:
🇺🇸

This weekend reminded me nothing is more precious than the life we were gifted and the relationships we’ve created. I’ll never take this shit for granted. We’re back baby

node.text:
Leg Day like a boss 💼

Wearing @youngla compression shorts • restocking 7/6 @ 12pm pst
💠 Use code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off 💠

Sorry everyone for being slow on videos recently. These videos take me a helllll of a long time to make and I’ve been working on some big new projects behind the scenes… namely my return to YouTube as well a completely new system that will allow me to create custom programs for clients on a much larger scale for a much much cheaper price. Helping my clients and followers reach their dream physiques is the pinnacle of my career and the most fulfilling feeling I’ve ever experienced, but I only have so much time in the day. I’ve had to further limit my coaching clients in order to make time for my future investments and myself, so this app is number 1 on my priority list and I couldn’t be more stoked to get this out to y’all asap🥳

1. Landmine Back Lunge - 3 x 10-12
2. Landmine Lateral Lunge - 3 x 8-10
3. Landmine Stiff-Leg Deadlift - 4 x 8-10 
4. Nonstop High-Bar Squat - 3 x 12-14
5. Mermaid Wide-Stance Toes-Out Hamstring Curl w/ Hold - 6 x 14-15
6. Single-Leg Weighted Calf Raise - 3 x 10-12, 3 x 20-22

Notes:
High-Bar Squat first. Rest in order. 2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 5 & 6 to failure.
-
💊@ehplabs Biggest Sale of the year is still live with up to 60% off summer bundles. Cop your supps before the sale is over🤘
💠 Use code ‘NYLE10’ for 10% off 💠
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine.

Notes:
Alternating Supinated Overhead Press first. Rest in order. 2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 1, 3, 4, & 5 to failure.

Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈

❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program. 

The easiest way to ensure you’re increasing volume is by keeping the exercises of each recurrence of that muscle group a constant (doing the same exercises at each recurrence) in order to eliminate exercise variance as a variable that could affect total volume of work done on that muscle group just by the nature of engaging in different exercises.
